---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NewsletterForm from '../components/NewsletterForm.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Zro2One" description="Why Zro2One exists and the story behind it.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 sm:py-24">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black text-zro-dark mb-8">
      Why Zro2One exists
    </h1>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        People keep asking me about AI.
      </p>
      <p>
        My mom wants to know if it's going to take her job. My friend who runs a marketing agency wants to know which tools to use. A developer I know wants to understand transformer architecture. A researcher wants my take on the latest papers.
      </p>
      <p>
        They're all asking about <strong>the same thing</strong> — but they need completely different answers.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's the problem with AI education today. It's either oversimplified clickbait ("AI will change EVERYTHING!") or impenetrable research papers. There's almost nothing in between. And what does exist rarely connects the dots between levels.
      </p>

      <h2>The Zro2One approach</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Zro2One</strong> (Zero to One) takes you from wherever you are to the next level of understanding. The name comes from the idea that the hardest part of learning is going from zero — knowing nothing — to one — having real, useful understanding.
      </p>
      <p>
        We explain the same topics at four depth levels:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>🟢 Essential</strong> — For anyone. Plain language, real analogies, no prerequisites.</li>
        <li><strong>🔵 Applied</strong> — For professionals. How to actually use AI in your work.</li>
        <li><strong>🟣 Technical</strong> — For builders. Architecture, code, implementation details.</li>
        <li><strong>🔴 Research</strong> — For researchers. Paper breakdowns, frontier concepts, open questions.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You pick your depth. You go as deep as you want. And when you're ready for more, the next level is always right there.
      </p>

      <h2>About Bee</h2>
      <p>
        I'm Bee, the founder of Zro2One. I've spent years at the intersection of AI and people — watching brilliant technology fail to reach the people who need it most. Not because people aren't smart enough, but because no one is meeting them where they are.
      </p>
      <p>
        AI is the most transformative technology of our lifetimes. And right now, understanding it is a privilege — available to those with the right technical background, the right Twitter follows, the right conference passes.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's not okay.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>AI literacy should be as accessible as regular literacy.</strong> A teacher in rural Texas should understand how the AI tools in her classroom work. A small business owner should know which AI tools are worth paying for. A policy maker should understand what they're regulating.
      </p>
      <p>
        Zro2One is my answer to that challenge. It's education that meets you where you are and takes you where you want to go. Zero to one.
      </p>

      <h2>The mission</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Democratize AI education for all of humanity.</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        Not just developers. Not just techies. Everyone. Because in a world being reshaped by AI, understanding it isn't optional — it's essential.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <NewsletterForm />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
